articles.description: Matt Mobley scored 30 points and grabbed nine rebounds, Jaylen Adams added 26 points with five assists and four steals and St. Bonaventure beat La Salle 79-68 on Tuesday night for its first seven-game Atlantic 10 winning streak in program history.
articles.headline: St. Bonaventure wins 7th straight A-10 game for 1st time

articles.description: Jaelen Sanford scored 21 points on 6-of-9 shooting and Tre'Shaun Fletcher had 17 points and eight rebounds to help Toledo beat Ohio 82-74 on Tuesday night for its fourth win in a row.
articles.headline: Sanford scores 21, Fletcher 17 as Toledo beats Ohio 82-74

articles.description: Matt Lewis halted a scoring drought, making two free throws in the final seconds, to give James Madison a 62-61 win over UNC Wilmington on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Lewis sinks late FTs, James Madison takes 62-61 victory

articles.description: Oklahoma's Trae Young cannot connect from behind the arc as the Sooner returns to his hometown to face Big 12 rivals Texas Tech in Lubbock.
articles.headline: Young struggles against Texas Tech

images.caption: Oklahoma's Trae Young cannot connect from behind the arc as the Sooner returns to his hometown to face Big 12 rivals Texas Tech in Lubbock.
images.name: Young struggles against Texas Tech

articles.description: Elijah Minnie tossed in 24 points and James Thompson IV finished with his 18th double-double of the season to help Eastern Michigan hold off Miami (Ohio) 58-57 on Tuesday night.
articles.headline: Eastern Michigan holds off Miami (OH) 58-57

articles.description: Udoka Azubuike scored 19 points, Malik Newman had 17 and 13th-ranked Kansas bounced back from a brutal loss at Baylor by beating Iowa State 83-77 on Tuesday.
articles.headline: No. 13 Kansas holds off Iowa State 83-77

images.caption: Lagerald Vick lobs it to Udoka Azubuike for another alley-oop.
images.name: Azubuike cannot be stopped

videos.description: KeVaughn Allen slips backdoor for a two-handed flush.
videos.headline: Florida's Allen throws down baseline dunk

videos.description: Texas A&M throws a bad pass in traffic and Florida collects the rebound, with Egor Koulechov knocking down a corner 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Turnover leads to Florida transition three

videos.description: Tonny Trocha-Morelos delivers a pass to Robert Williams underneath the basket for a two-handed flush.
videos.headline: Texas A&M's Williams dunks it with power

videos.description: Jay Jay Chandler drills a corner 3-pointer with one second left on the shot clock.
videos.headline: Texas A&M's Chandler just beats buzzer for 3-pointer

videos.description: Florida head coach Mike White says his team's ability to get stops on the defensive end has helped the Gators build a 16-point halftime lead.
videos.headline: White: Florida is playing with 'confidence'

videos.description: Kevarrius Hayes rolls to the basket and recieves a pass from Chris Chiozza for an alley-oop dunk.
videos.headline: Florida's Hayes gets alley-oop off pick-and-roll

videos.description: Chris Chiozza drives baseline and delivers a wraparound pass to Egor Koulechov for a 3-pointer.
videos.headline: Chiozza gets fancy for Florida 3-pointer

videos.description: Kevarrius Hayes cleans up the miss and punishes the rim with an emphatic two-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Florida's Hayes shakes the backboard with monstrous putback dunk

videos.description: Mike White calls Florida's win over No. 11 Texas A&M a big win and says the Gators' defense is better than a month ago.
videos.headline: White pleased with Florida's 'fight' in win

videos.description: Egor Koulechov says Florida talk during halftime to make sure they didn't give up another halftime time lead like they've done in the past.
videos.headline: Koulechov: Florida was mentally locked in

videos.description: Jay Bilas credits Florida's shooting and ability to take care of the ball in its win over No.11 Texas A&M.
videos.headline: Florida now 2-0 in conference play after win

videos.description: Unranked Florida makes 17 shots from behind the arc in Tuesday night's SEC matchup to beat Texas A&M 83-66.
videos.headline: Gators upset No. 11 Aggies on the road
